Welcome to the Study Hall community!

Study Hall is a tailored series of YouTube Learning Playlists designed to guide you as you consider transitioning to or beginning your college experience.

Navigate your pathway to college

Study Hall helps you understand how to explore majors and fields of study, navigate college and get an early start on your college education.

  • Videos

    Watch engaging new videos weekly and learn more about the subject at hand.

  • Resources

    Download useful checklists, guides and additional materials that dive deeper into tips for success.

  • Shorts

    Get your questions answered through quick bites of instruction. For more personalized shorts, share a little about your educational interests.

  • Community

    Embrace the Study Hall community. Subscribe to our YouTube channel and interact with Study Hall users across the globe.

Shape the future of Study Hall

How to contribute

Step 1: Subscribe to the Study Hall channel.

Step 2: Watch videos that address your interests and comment on your favorites.

In the coming weeks, we’ll be reaching out for specific information using the email address you provide.

Study Hall offerings

How to College

The How to College series was created to answer your questions surrounding college. From explaining what college is to walking you through the application process and discussing finances, we're here to guide you to and through your educational journey.

Learn more

Fast Guides

The Fast Guides series outlines what you’ll learn in some of the most popular majors in the U.S. and touches on related careers. Featured majors include psychology, English, nursing and interdisciplinary studies.

Learn more

Foundational topics

This series of educational learning playlists is designed to support you regardless of where and how you’re furthering your education. With premium learning content on topics ranging from chemistry and data literacy to composition and algebra, we have something for everyone.

Chemistry

In this playlist, hosted by Dr. Will Comar, you’ll break down different areas of chemistry. Learn more

Learn more

Data literacy

Data is everywhere. In this 15-episode playlist, your host Jessica Pucci walks you through ways to think about the data you’re presented with. Learn more

Learn more

Composition

Hosted by Yumna Samie, the goal of this playlist is to make writing easier. Learn writing techniques and improve your overall writing skills. Learn more

Learn more

Algebra

James Tanton guides you through solving equations and understanding how math works with our very human brains. Learn more

Learn more
